# Workshop data boundaries

- Participant data lives in `data/public.csv` (labeled) and `data/private.csv` (unlabeled).
- Do not read, open, or infer contents of `data/organizer/` — it is blocked by `.cursorignore` and contains private ground truth.
- Do not attempt to score models on the private set. Help participants train on public data and write `predictions.csv` for organizer scoring.
- Do not recreate or merge the full dataset from public + private labels.
